    "note": "Stage-8 (Fable) adjudication — full sweep of all 100 rows (structure: relative pronouns who/which/that/whose). Answers lens verified the structure: who/that=people, which/that=things/animals, whose=possession; all distractors (which-for-person, who-for-thing, what, who's-for-whose) genuinely wrong. Translation CLEAN (the deToEn-had-German bug was fixed for district/square/tower → all deToEn now English, re-confirmed). Fixed: register 6 (\"Anschlusswort\"/\"Nomen\" German category terms in prompts → \"Wort\"/named the pronouns); answers 1 (sb.001 ambiguous chips → added the buildable \"Who is the woman that lives here?\"); level-gloss 1 (government \"run a country\" → \"lead\"); a stale ec.003 explainDe (\"grandparents\"→\"king\"). Dropped an invalid English↔German matching-pairs (mp.002 — the German right-sides got gated). ~65 audited grants (relative-clause content verbs/nouns + London-theme carriers). 0 fix, 0 drop → approve."
